                            },
                            {
                                "tagType": "p",
                                "tagHTML": "The Nav Tattva, or nine fundamentals, are the essence of Jain philosophy. They explain the theory of karma, which is the basis for understanding how a soul can achieve liberation (Moksh). By understanding these principles, we can learn how to stop new karma from coming in (<strong>Samvar</strong>) and how to remove old karma (<strong>Nirjar√§</strong>)."
